parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without pressing the accelerator pedal
making it difficult to stop or control the vehicle. The brakes may not function properly
and the vehicle may continue to accelerate even when shifted into park or neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to disengage
causing the vehicle to accelerate suddenly and uncontrollably. The vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the brakes are applied
and the driver may need to turn off the ignition to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle sticking can cause the vehicle to accelerate suddenly and uncontrollably, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The throttle pedal sticks or gets stuck

and the driver may need to turn off the ignition to stop the vehicle.
